@* A field the template reads ONLY through a METHOD it calls (register A14; the S10 slice). `count` is
   named nowhere in the template -- it is read by `Format()`, which the `@Format()` slot calls, and it
   is written by the `@onclick` handler. Decision 67's conjunction (read AND written) must still lift
   it, so the read is propagated through the call graph: a field a template-called method reads is a
   field the template reads, one hop further than decision 160's computed transitivity. `count` becomes
   `signal(0)`, `Format()` reads `count.value`, and `@Format()` is a live effect that moves on #inc.
   Before the fix `count` stayed a plain `let` and the display, inserted once, froze at "n=0". *@
<p><span id="n">@Format()</span></p>
<button id="inc" @onclick="Bump">inc</button>

@code {
    private int count = 0;

    private string Format()
    {
        return $"n={count}";
    }

    void Bump()
    {
        count++;
    }
}
